<paragraph blockId="33.[189,1399,1038,1134]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
The three specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[521,675,1038,1064]" name="South Africa" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">South Africa</collectingCountry>
have the head differently colored, with face blackish, and mandible and orbits yellow. Furthermore, the dorsal edge of clypeus is densely punctate. They are otherwise strictly similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[561,664,1108,1134]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">holotype</typeStatus>
and are included as non-type specimens.
</paragraph>
